                            <comment id="16949841" author="ableegoldman" created="Fri, 11 Oct 2019 23:42:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=abellemare&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;abellemare&quot;&gt;abellemare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vvcephei&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vvcephei&quot;&gt;vvcephei&lt;/a&gt; Can you take a look?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16951519" author="vvcephei" created="Tue, 15 Oct 2019 03:05:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll pick this one up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve reproduced the issue. The root cause is that we shouldn&apos;t ask serdes to de/serialize `null` values in  a KTable context, but we do in this case. I&apos;ll work on a PR asap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16951528" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 15 Oct 2019 03:18:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;vvcephei commented on pull request #7518: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9032&quot; title=&quot;Serializer is invoked with null when foreignValue=null&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-9032&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-9032&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Bypass serdes for tombstones&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7518&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7518&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   In a KTable context, null record values have a special &quot;tombstone&quot; significance. We should always bypass the serdes for such tombstones, since otherwise the serde could violate Streams&apos; table semantics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   I&apos;ve added test coverage for this case and fixed the code accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

